						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">raydempsey wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I'm not worried about putting it on a cart later because I can't profit off of my game because of the NFL trademarks.</div><br />So if you can't sell the game and the existing Flash carts don't have good support for the MMC5, are people stuck with running it on emulators unless they decide to build a cart themselves from an MMC5 donor?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">The instructions says that for CHR MODE 3, I will need to write to $5130 for the upper bank bits and between $5120-$5127 for the lower bank bits. So to switch $0000-$03FF bank 12C, would I have to write #$01 to $5130 first then #$2C to $5120?</div><br />Yes, that seems correct. There's no &quot;master banking&quot; like I thought there was, so you can freely mix and match tiles from all 1024 banks.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">If I have 1024K CHR ROM, which 16384 tiles do I have access to?</div><br />Well, then $5130 starts to act as a master bank selection register. It selects which group of 16384 tiles will be used, and you can't mix tiles from different groups. I'm not sure how that affects sprites, though...</div>

